I am trying to record responses from a 3-button mouse into a .zil file. My
problem is that the input from one of the buttons is not recording. In the
TimeDx PIO test, this button registers as Input Bit 4 (VOX). The other two
buttons (Input Bit 1 (NEG) and Input Bit 2 (POS)) are recording perfectly.  
Is there something I'm lacking in my command line that would enable input
from this button?

Here's my command line:

N26 <zil> <ContinuousRun> <t 1800> <defaultwritingcolor 255255255> 0
<nofeedback> <defaultbackgroundcolor 0>  <defaultfont Times New Roman>
<defaultfontsize 26> <id keyboard> <id PIO12> <d 0> <RecordClockOnTime>
<TimeCriticalFrame> <vm 640,480,480,16,0>

